The paper discusses the migration of robots into sensitive home settings and the ethical considerations surrounding their use. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and fair information practices, which are relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-category. The paper also discusses the importance of research ethics and human subjects research frameworks, which are relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also touches on the potential vulnerabilities of certain individuals, such as children, disabled, or elderly persons, which is relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of technology development, which is relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
